[
  {
    "text": "Demonstration of DOCX support in",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Demonstration of DOCX support in",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "calibre",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "This document demonstrates the ability of the calibre DOCX Input plugin to",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "convert the various typographic features in a Microsoft Word (2007 and newer)",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "document. Convert this document to a modern ebook format, such as AZW3 for",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Kindles or EPUB for other ebook readers, to see it in action.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "There is support for images, tables, lists, footnotes, endnotes, links, dropcaps and",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "various types of text and paragraph level formatting.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "To see the DOCX conversion in action, simply add this file to calibre using the",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "“Add Books” button and then click “ Convert”. Set the output format in the top right",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "corner of the conversion dialog to EPUB or AZW3 and click “OK” .",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "calibre",
      "pageNumber": 1
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Text Formatting",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Inline formatting",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Here, we demonstrate various types of inline text formatting and the use of",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "embedded fonts.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Here is some bold, italic, bold-italic, underlined and struck out text. Then, we",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "have a super script and a sub script . Now we see some red, green and blue text. Some text",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "with a yellow highlight. Some text in a box. Some text in inverse video.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "A paragraph with styled text: subtle emphasis followed by strong text and",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "intense emphasis . This paragraph uses document wide styles for styling rather than",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "inline text properties as demonstrated in the previous paragraph — calibre can handle",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "both with equal ease.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Fun with fonts",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "This document has embedded the Ubuntu font family. The body text is in the",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Ubuntu typeface, here is some text in the Ubuntu Mono typeface, notice how every",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "letter has the same width, even i and m . Every embedded font will automatically",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "be embedded in the output ebook during conversion.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Paragraph level formatting",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "You can do crazy things with paragraphs, if the urge strikes you. For instance this",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "paragraph is right aligned and has a right border. It has also been given a light gray",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "background.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "For the lovers of poetry amongst you, paragraphs with hanging indents, like this often",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "come in handy. You can use hanging indents to ensure that a line of poetry",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "retains its individual identity as a line even when the screen is too narrow to",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "display it as a single line. Not only does this paragraph have a hanging indent, it",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "is also has an extra top margin, setting it apart from the preceding paragraph.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Text Formatting",
      "pageNumber": 2
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Tables",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "ITEM NEEDED Tables in Word can vary from the extremely",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Books 1 simple to the extremely complex. calibre tries to do",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Pens 3",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Pencils 2",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "its best when converting tables. While you may run",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Highlighter 2 colors into trouble with the occasional table, the vast",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Scissors 1 pair majority of common cases should be converted very",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "well, as demonstrated in this section. Note that for",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "optimum results, when creating tables in Word, you should set their widths using",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "percentages, rather than absolute units. To the left of this paragraph is a floating two",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "column table with a nice green border and header row.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Now let’s look at a fancier table— one with alternating row colors and partial",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "borders. This table is stretched out to take 100% of the available width.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "City or Point A Point B Point C Point D Point E",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Town",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Point A —",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Point B 87 —",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Point C 64 56 —",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Point D 37 32 91 —",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Point E 93 35 54 43 —",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Next, we see a table with special formatting in various locations. Notice how the",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "formatting for the header row and sub header rows is preserved.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "College New students Graduating Change",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Tables",
      "pageNumber": 3
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "students",
    "metadata": {
