  {
    "text": "Structural Elements",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Miscellaneous structural elements you can add to your document, like footnotes,",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "endnotes, dropcaps and the like.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Footnotes & Endnotes",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Footnotes 1 and endnotes i are automatically recognized and both are converted to",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "endnotes, with backlinks for maximum ease of use in ebook devices.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Dropcaps",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "rop caps are used to emphasize the leading paragraph at the start of a",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "section. In Word it is possible to specify how many lines of text a drop-cap",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "Structural Elements",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "D should use.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Links",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Two kinds of links are possible, those that refer to an external website and those",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "that refer to locations inside the document itself. Both are supported by calibre. For",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "example, here is a link pointing to the calibre download page . Then we have a link that",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "points back to the section on paragraph level formatting in this document.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Table of Contents",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "You can see the Table of Contents created by calibre by clicking the Table of",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Contents button in whatever viewer you are using to view the converted ebook.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "pdf",
      "closestHeading": "D should use.",
      "pageNumber": 5
    }
  },
